snippet.textDisplay:
We'll have to see how far the difference between personal sales and sales to companies turn out.
AMD could win because their CPUs are geared towards gaming and personal use with their advantage on single core. Better for budget builds and gaming.
Intel however still seems to have the lead when it comes to multicore which is used for all kinds of renderings and whatnot. Better for professional work stations.
I do think AMD will win in the end though.  They still sell high end processors for workstations that are cheaper than Intel, could have a lot of smaller businesses using AMD soon to make up the difference.
